.TH xsetpointa 1 "xsetpointa 1.0.1" "X Version 11"
.SH NAME
xsetpointa \- set a X Input thang as tha main pointer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xsetpointa \-l
|
.I device-name
.SH DESCRIPTION
Xsetpointa sets a XInput thang as tha main pointer n' shit.  When called with
the \-l flag it lists tha available devices.  When called wit tha -c/+c
flag, it togglez tha bustin  of core input events, fo' servers which
implement a virtual core pointer; -c disablez core events, n' +c enables.
